

AWS has differenct ways of managing users of your web app

CloudFront signed URLs

signed cookies

both have the same basic functionality, however:

signed URLs are used for:  
 - RTMP distributions, signed cookies do not support these.  
 - restricting access to individual files such as app installation downloads
 - if used do not have a client that supports cookies
 
signed cookies can be used:
 - when multiple restricted file access is to be provided
 - current URLs should not change
 

CloudFront with Match Viewer (an ORIGIN Protocol Policy) communicates with your origin using HTTP or HTTPS

CloudFront with Field-Level Encryption will only alloy secure upload to web servers, and not downloads

