if you have a social media website that uses CloudFront and users are experiencing delays in logging in and HTTP 504 errors

Lambda@Edge allows you to run Lambda functions to customise content that CloudFront delivers - with execution occuring closer to the user.

Lambda functions can be used to changeCloudFront requests and responses:

 - after CloudFront receives a request form a viewer
 - Before CF receives a request to the origin
 - Afrer CF forwards the request to the origin
 - Before CF forwards response to the viewer
 
 
 
 to avoid slow login times and 504 messages
 
 customised CF web dist. content usitn Lambda@Edge - allow Lambda functions to execute auth process in users' locations
 
 set up an origin failover by creating an origin group with 2. origins, one as primary origin, secondary is switched to automatically is specific HTTP status is returned
 
 geographically dispersed VPCs are more expensive to set up and maintain
 
 login is not caching of a static object
 
 using Route53 to route incoming traffic to lowest latency is significantly more expensive
 
 References:

https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonCloudFront/latest/DeveloperGuide/high_availability_origin_failover.html

